            "contents": "\"There is no greater teacher than experience.\" - Unknown\n\n\"Live as if you were to die tomorrow. Learn as if you were to live forever.\" - Mahatma Gandhi\n\n\"The only true wisdom is in knowing you know nothing.\" - Socrates\n\nYou are the only one who can teach yourself. No one else can do it for you.\n\nThis may seem like a strange thing to say, but it's true. Every single person is responsible for their own education. We may have teachers and mentors who can guide us, but ultimately, it is up to us to learn.\n\nThis is because learning is not a passive process. It is an active process. We learn by doing, by experiencing, by making mistakes. No one can teach us everything we need to know. We have to learn for ourselves.\n\nThis can be a scary thought. It means that we are responsible for our own lives. It means that we can't blame others for our mistakes. It means that we have to take risks.\n\nHowever, it also means that we are in control of our own lives. We get to choose what we want to learn. We get to choose what we want to do with our lives. We get to make our own decisions.\n\nThis is a liberating thought. It means that we are not limited by what others think we should do. It means that we are free to be our own person. It means that we can create our own destiny.\n\nSo, if you want to change your life, change the way you learn. Stop waiting for someone else to teach you what you need to know. Start learning for yourself. Start taking risks. Start making mistakes. And most importantly, start living your life.",
