            "contents": "Mindfulness is the practice of being present in the here and now. It is the active side of meditation - it is what we do when we are out in the world. Mindfulness helps us to be more aware of our thoughts and emotions, and it helps us to be more present for all the moments in our lives.\n\nThere are many ways to be more mindful throughout your day:\n\n1) Pay attention to your thoughts and emotions: Notice when you are feeling stressed or anxious, and take a few deep breaths.\n2) Pay attention to your surroundings: Notice the sights and sounds around you, and take a few deep breaths.\n3) Pay attention to your body: Notice how your body feels, and take a few deep breaths.\n4) Pay attention to your breath: Notice your breath going in and out, and take a few deep breaths.\n5) Connect with your senses: Notice what you can see, smell, taste, touch, and feel. Take a few deep breaths.\n6) Be in the moment: Don't focus on the past or the future - be present in the here and now. Take a few deep breaths.\n\nMindfulness is the key to living an intentional life. It is the practice of being present in the here and now. It helps us to be more aware of our thoughts and emotions, and it helps us to be more present for all the moments in our lives.",
